SUMMARY:Staying Essential: How Leadership Protects and Advances Your Career
DESCRIPTION:Come and join us to explore why technical skills and hard work alone are no longer enough in an era shaped by AI\, layoffs\, and constant change. This session examines how leadership thinking — regardless of title — becomes the most durable form of career security\, and how judgment\, influence\, and long-term value creation distinguish professionals who continue to advance from those who become replaceable. Through candid insights and real-world perspectives\, the discussion will help professionals at all stages rethink how to build resilience\, relevance\, and sustained career growth in today’s workforce. \n​Speaker Intro: \n​Melody Zhang\nChief Human Resources Officer\, Providence Swedish (U.S.)\nRecognized as one of the Top 50 Women CHROs of 2025 by Women We Admire\nPreviously held senior HR leadership roles at AB InBev and The Hershey Company \n​Providence Swedish is part of Providence\, a $100B+ nonprofit health system\, making it one of the largest and most financially powerful healthcare networks in the United States\, with 8 hospitals and 22\,000+ caregivers in Western Washington.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/staying-essential-how-leadership-protects-and-advances-your-career/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Screenshot-2026-02-02-095723-1-e1770055212144.png
END:VEVENT
