SUMMARY:AI-assisted coding in practice: successes\, failures\, and engineering trade-offs
DESCRIPTION:AI-assisted coding tools are becoming part of everyday development workflows. From IDE assistants to chat-based helpers\, many teams already rely on them to write\, refactor\, and review code. Yet real-world usage often reveals trade-offs that are not obvious in demos or marketing materials.\nThis webinar takes a practical\, experience-driven look at how AI tools are actually used in software development today\, where they deliver measurable value\, where they fall short\, and what engineering teams should consider before relying on them at scale. \nRather than focusing on specific vendors or tools\, the session explores tool-agnostic patterns\, workflow implications\, and architectural considerations observed in real projects. \nWhat we’ll cover:\nCommon AI coding tools and how teams use them in practice\nWhere AI fits in the coding lifecycle—and where it doesn’t\nProductivity gains: what can be measured versus what is only perceived\nIntegrating AI into existing development workflows (local dev\, PRs\, CI)\nSecurity\, compliance\, and intellectual property considerations \nThis session is designed for teams reviewing their current use of AI in development or considering wider adoption. It will help you understand which coding tasks benefit from AI assistance\, how to integrate these tools into existing workflows\, and what to watch for from a quality\, security\, and maintainability perspective.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/ai-assisted-coding-in-practice-successes-failures-and-engineering-trade-offs/
LOCATION:Online
CATEGORIES:Artificial Intelligence,Developer
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/AI-assisted-coding-webinar.png
ORGANIZER;CN="CIGen.io Azure Consulting and Development Company":MAILTO:contact@cigen.me
END:VEVENT
