SUMMARY:Eastside Marketing Morning Brew Meetup
DESCRIPTION:Marketing keeps changing fast. New tools. New algorithms. New ideas. And the best way to keep up isn’t by competing over who’s doing the best. It’s by learning together. \nWhen someone shares what worked for them and what didn’t\, everyone benefits. That’s the power of showing up honestly. \nIf you want genuine conversations\, come join us. \nWe’ll have some light snacks and free parking available. \nHow it works?\n1. Write down a topic\n2. Vote on what to cover\n3. 10 minutes per topic\n(plus 5 minutes if the group agrees) \nWhat people usually get out of it?\n1. A place to test thoughts\nYou can float ideas you might not say in a meeting and get real reactions from peers. \n2. A break from the bubble\nIt helps to talk with people who aren’t in your org. You get different angles you wouldn’t hear internally. \n3. A few new faces\nNot in a transactional sense. Just new people doing similar work.
URL:https://www.geekwire.com/calendar-event/eastside-marketing-morning-brew-meetup-3/
LOCATION:Beyondsoft Consulting Inc.\, 2010 156th Ave NE\, Bellevue\, 98007\, United States
CATEGORIES:Brand Marketing,Meetups
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://cdn.geekwire.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/Feb-2026-Meetup.jpeg
ORGANIZER;CN="Beyondsoft Consulting Inc":MAILTO:marketing@us.beyondsoft.com
END:VEVENT
